## Test Protocol

Each law is encoded as a squared deviation constraint parameterized by λ ∈ [0, 1].

At λ = 1 (on manifold): deviation → 0 for every law.
At λ = 0 (off manifold): deviation > 0 for every law.

Every possible triple (50 choose 3 = 19,600 combinations) was tested. For each triple, the sum of squared deviations was computed on and off the manifold.

Pass condition: on-manifold deviation < 10⁻²⁰ AND off-manifold deviation > 10⁻²⁰.

